#include<cstdio>
inline int min(int a,int b)
{
    if(a<b)
    return a;
    else
    return b;
}
inline int max(int a,int b)
{
    if(a>b)
    return a;
    else
    return b;
}
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int test;
    int x[2][2],y[2][2],ans[2][2];
    scanf("%d",&test);
    while(test--)
    {
        scanf("%d %d %d %d",&x[0][0],&y[0][0],&x[0][1],&y[0][1]);
        scanf("%d %d %d %d",&x[1][0],&y[1][0],&x[1][1],&y[1][1]);
        if((x[0][1]<=x[1][0])||(x[0][0]>=x[1][1])||(y[0][1]<=y[1][0])||(y[0][0]>=y[1][1]))
        printf("No Overlap\n");
        else
        {
            ans[0][0]=max(x[0][0],x[1][0]);
            ans[1][0]=min(x[0][1],x[1][1]);
            ans[0][1]=max(y[0][0],y[1][0]);
            ans[1][1]=min(y[0][1],y[1][1]);
            printf("%d %d %d %d\n",ans[0][0],ans[0][1],ans[1][0],ans[1][1]);
        }

    }
    return 0;
}
